metadata.title: Diamond DA42 Twin Star
aws::graph::propositions: DA42 is a production aircraft built in Austria and Canada.
DA42 M is a Special Mission variant built in Austria and China.
DA42 M is a modification from standard DA42 and new production.
DA42 L360 is equipped with Lycoming IO-360 134 kW (180 hp) engines.
DA42 L360 uses 100LL fuel instead of Jet-A1.
DA42 L360 is intended for the North American flight training market.
DA42 NG is equipped with Austro Engine AE 300 127 kW (170 hp) engines.
DA42 NG was EASA certified in March 2009.
DA42 NG was FAA certified in April 2010.
DA42 NG was Transport Canada certified on 16 April 2012.
DA42 NG production aircraft have been built in Austria, Canada, China and Russia.
DA42 M-NG is a Special Mission variant of the NG.
DA42 MPP is a Multi Purpose Platform variant.
DA42 MPP is modified to carry aerial sensing, mapping and surveillance payloads.
Diamond Airborne Sensing produces the MPP variant.
Diamond Airborne Sensing is a wholly owned subsidiary of Diamond.

text:
## Variants

DA42
Production aircraft built in Austria and Canada
DA42 M
Special Mission variant built in Austria and China, modification from standard DA42 and new production.
DA42 L360
Lycoming IO-360 134 kW (180 hp) equipped version using 100LL fuel instead of Jet-A1. This model is intended for the North American flight training market.
DA42 NG
Austro Engine AE 300 127 kW (170 hp) equipped version. EASA certified March 2009; FAA certified April 2010; Transport Canada certified 16 April 2012. Production aircraft have been built in Austria, Canada, China and Russia.
DA42 M-NG
Special Mission variant of the NG.
DA42 MPP
Diamond Airborne Sensing a wholly owned subsidiary of Diamond produces the MPP or "Multi Purpose Platform" variant which is modified to carry aerial sensing, mapping and surveillance payloads.
